                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11 Am 8/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-15T11:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1921—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 16—7:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. My 33, November 14th, 11 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m</hi>]<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d802fn1">Not printed.</note> I had an interview with President
                    yesterday afternoon. He stated that the president of the council of Guayaquil
                    had informed him that the municipality has sufficient money set aside to pay
                    Amsinck claim but that United <pb facs="0997" n="873" xml:id="pg_873"/> States
                    drafts cannot be obtained. He said that he believes present members of municipal
                    council are acting in good faith. I suggest that Amsinck and Company arrange to
                    receive payment in sucres at such rate as may be agreed upon and have same
                    deposited to their credit in some bank in Ecuador until such time as United
                    States drafts can be obtained. This will prevent possible diversion of funds to
                    other purposes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
